description:
Inserting data to the default graph doesn't work.
Running the following query as specified in the SPARQL 1.1 standard (http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-sparql11-update-20130321/#insertData, Example 1):
PREFIX dc: <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/>
INSERT DATA
{
  <http://example/book1> dc:title "A new book" ;
                         dc:creator "A.N.Other" .
}

results in an error:
Virtuoso 37000 Error SP031: SPARQL compiler: No default graph specified in the preamble, but it is needed for triple in INSERT DATA {...} without GRAPH {...}

SPARQL query:
define sql:big-data-const 0
#output-format:text/html
define sql:signal-void-variables 1 PREFIX dc: <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/>
INSERT DATA
{
  <http://example/book1> dc:title "A new book" ;
                         dc:creator "A.N.Other" .
}

poc:
PREFIX dc: <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/>
INSERT DATA {
  GRAPH <urn:sparql:tests:insert:data> {
    <http://example/book1> dc:title "A new book" ;
                             dc:creator "A.N.Other" .
  }
}
